                        Senator Austin</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d125</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">125</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB/11–2246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Senator <persName type="to">Austin</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-11-22T19:00:00-05:00">November 22, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>293. For <gloss target="#t_Gadel1">Gadel</gloss>. Our reasons for preferring
                    Netherlands to Byelorussia as candidate for <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss> are set out below for your consideration when subject is
                    next discussed by Secretary and <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>: (1)
                    Among remaining candidates for three-year membership on <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss>, Netherlands is only state willing and
                    able to collaborate wholeheartedly in creation and implementation of <gloss target="#t_ITO1">ITO</gloss>, in our view, most important tasks to be
                    undertaken by <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss>. (2) Netherlands has
                    demonstrated unswerving fidelity to western democratic principles in all organs
                    UN and Van Kleffens has made particularly notable contribution to work of <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>. In view this record, failure of US to support
                    Netherlands might have adverse reaction not only upon Netherlands but upon other
                    small western European states as well.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
